'''Lynn Wells''' was a [[civil rights]] activist in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] during the 1960s and was a member of the [[Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee]] (SNCC), the [[Southern Student Organizing Committee]] (SSOC), and then a national leader of [[Students for a Democratic Society (1960 organization)|Students for a Democratic Society]] and the [[Revolutionary Youth Movement]] in the late 1960s. <ref>{{cite journal | url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/When+community+comes+home+to+roost:+the+southern+milltown+as+Lost...-a0152922869 | title=When community comes home to roost: the southern milltown as Lost Cause. | author=Fink, Leon | journal=Journal of Social History |date=September 2006 | volume=22}}</ref>

Today, She is now the Director of the Cooleemee Historical Association and the mayor of Cooleemee, North Carolina.

